The paper deals with algorithms for external-memory sorting, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the first phase of external-memory sorting, which is run generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions online algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AL (Algorithms). The paper also mentions resource augmentation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions the concept of competitiveness, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
